&lt;P CLASS="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;FONT SIZE="2"&gt;The capacity to make ideas happen is a combination of three
            key elements: &lt;EM&gt;Organization + Communal Forces + Leadership Capability.&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal;"&gt; This &lt;SPAN CLASS="il"&gt;session&lt;/SPAN&gt;, based on the research in Behance
            founder Scott Belsky’s &lt;A HREF="http://www.amazon.com/Making-Ideas-Happen-Overcoming-Obstacles/dp/159184312X/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;s=books&amp;qid=1260382822&amp;sr=8-1" TARGET="_blank"&gt;forthcoming
            book&lt;/A&gt;, will focus on the third component of making ideas happen: Leadership
            Capability.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
            &lt;P CLASS="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;FONT SIZE="2"&gt;The scalability of any great creative endeavor ultimately
            depends upon your ability to lead. We’ll discuss the particular challenges of
            managing and incentivizing a creative team, the importance of creating an
            unorthodox rewards system, and the skills you’ll need to build for sustained
            self-leadership. Tips and insights that we’ll review include:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
            &lt;UL STYLE="margin-top: 0in;" TYPE="disc"&gt;
            &lt;LI CLASS="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;FONT SIZE="2"&gt;Short-circuiting
            the traditional rewards system&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;
            &lt;LI CLASS="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;FONT SIZE="2"&gt;Engaging
            “initiators” in your creative pursuits&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;
            &lt;LI CLASS="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;FONT SIZE="2"&gt;Developing
            others through the power of appreciation&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;
            &lt;LI CLASS="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;FONT SIZE="2"&gt;Sharing
            ownership of your ideas&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;
            &lt;LI CLASS="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;FONT SIZE="2"&gt;Combating
            conventional wisdom&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;
            &lt;/UL&gt;
            &lt;P CLASS="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;FONT SIZE="2"&gt;After the presentation, we’ll open up the floor for best
            practices sharing and refinement amongst the group. A tour of the Behance
        office and wine reception will follow.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;

